		<li><a name="gary_1963"></a>Gary, N.E. 1963. Observations of mating behavior in the honeybee. J. Apic. Res. 2: 3-9.</li>
		<li><a name="koeniger_koeniger_fabritius_1979"></a>Koeniger, G., N. Koeniger, &amp; M. Fabritius. 1979. Some detailed observations of mating in the honeybee. Bee World 60: 53-57.</li>
		<li><a name="laidlaw_page_1984"></a>Laidlaw, H.H., R.E. Page. 1984. Polyandry in honey bees (<i>Apis mellifera</i> L.): sperm utilization and intracolony genetic relationships. Genetics 108: 985-997.</li>
		<li><a name="page_metcalf_1982"></a>Page, R.E. &amp; R.A. Metcalf. 1982. Multiple mating, sperm utilization, and social evolution. Am. Nat. 119: 263-281.</li>
		<li><a name="starr_1984"></a>Starr, C.K. 1984. Sperm competition, kinship, and sociality in the aculeate Hymenoptera, pp. 428-464. In R.L. Smith [ed.], Sperm competition and the evolution of animal mating systems. Academic Press, Orlando, Florida.</li>
		<li><a name="winston_1987"></a>Winston, M.L. 1987. The biology of the honey bee. Harvard University Press, Cambridge, Massachusetts.</li>
		<li><a name="woyke_1962"></a>Woyke, J. 1962. Natural and artificial insemination of queen honeybees. Bee World 43: 21-25.</li>
		<li>Woyke, J. &amp; F. Ruttner. 1958. An anatomical study of the mating process in the honeybee. Bee World 39: 3-18.</li>
	</ul>
	
